Item Description 1989 Fender American Plus Stratocaster Electric Guitar in very good condition. The guitar has some smaller, light dings and scratches on the front. The back and edges also have scratches and dings. (PLEASE SEE PICTURES). Beautiful and not too common Blue Pearl Burst finish with a white pickguard and chrome hardware. The guitar has a nice action and the "C" profile one piece maple necks has a great feel. The 87-89 neck profiles had a great degree of variance and this neck is one of the thinner varieties. The fretboard has a 9.5" radius and is 1.687" at the nut. The frets are in very good condition with very light grooving under the plain strings in the first position. The 2 Fender Silver Lace Sensor pickups in the neck and middle with a Blue Lace Sensor in the bridge have a good tone and output. The TBX tone circuit lets you get the most of these pickups. The guitar is equipped with a Wilkinson roller nut, locking tuners and Trem-Setter bridge stabilizer(currently the bridge is pulled down to the body). This guitar looks, sounds and plays great. Includes the Fender hard shell case, tremolo arm and strap. Serial Number: E910749 Weight: 8 lbs. 5 oz.
